<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 9200 9300 9400 MODELS BUILT AFTER JANUARY 1, 1995 - ELECTRONIC
        ENGINE CONTROLS - CATERPILLAR - 1992-1993 - TROUBLESHOOTING - CLUTCH SWITCH
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CLUTCH SWITCH</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If the vehicle is equipped with an Allison WT transmission, this switch is replaced with a
                        jumper connection.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>Before beginning this test procedure, inspect all connectors for loose or damaged pins, wires,
                        etc. (Refer to
                        <hotlnk document="s08145_18.xml" xrefid="x0814507">Inspecting Connectors</hotlnk>.)
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Clutch Switch And Circuits</title>
            <figure id="f0814516" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0814516" filename="../figg08/G0814516.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption></caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0814517" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0814517" filename="../figg08/G0814517.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption></caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Adjusting Clutch Switch</title>
            <para>The clutch switch should be mounted so that the switch actuator makes contact with the clutch pedal
                arm when the arm is depressed 0.5 inches at the point of actuator contact. The bracket can be bent
                forward or backward for adjustment. An audible click (switch closing) should be heard when the pedal is
                released.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
